NCT00039832.inclusion:
The eligibility criteria provided contains 36 criteria:

INCLUSION CRITERIA:
1. Diagnosis of acute ischemic stroke with onset between 3 and 24 hours prior to planned start of study drugs.
2. Disabling neurological deficit attributable to the acute stroke at the start of study drugs.
3. NIHSS less than or equal to 16.
4. Evidence on PWI MRI of a perfusion defect corresponding to the acute stroke syndrome of at least 2cm in diameter in both long and short axis in any slice.
5. Age 18 - 80 years, inclusive.

EXCLUSION CRITERIA:
6. Current participation in another study with an investigational drug or device within, prior participation in the present study, or planned participation in another therapeutic trial, prior to the final assessment in this trial.
7. Time interval since stroke onset of less than 24 hours impossible to determine with high degree of confidence.
8. Symptoms suggestive of subarachnoid hemorrhage, even if CT or MRI scan is negative for hemorrhage.
9. Evidence of acute myocardial infarction defined as having at least two of the following three features: 1.) Chest pain suggestive of cardiac ischemia; 2.) EKG findings of ST elevation of greater than 0.2 mV in 2 contiguous leads, new onset left bundle branch block, ST segment depression, or T-wave inversion; 3.) Elevated troponin I
10. Contraindication to MRI scan.
11. Women known to be pregnant, lactating or having a positive or indeterminate pregnancy test.
12. Patients who would refuse blood transfusions if medically indicated.
13. Neurological deficit that has led to stupor or coma (NIHSS level of consciousness score greater than or equal to 2).
14. High clinical suspicion of septic embolus.
15. Minor stroke with non-disabling deficit or rapidly improving neurological symptoms.
16. Baseline NIHSS greater than 16.
17. Evidence of acute or chronic ICH by head CT or MRI.
18. Evidence of microbleed on gradient echo MRI (GRE).
19. CT or MRI evidence of non-vascular cause for the neurological symptoms.
20. Signs of mass effect causing shift of midline structures.
21. Incomplete or uninterpretable DWI and PWI.
22. DWI abnormality larger than approximately one third of the territory of the middle cerebral artery territory by qualitative assessment.
23. Satellite DWI hyperintensity with corresponding hyperintensity on T2 weighted image or FLAIR in a vascular territory different than the index stroke (this is evidence of a new ischemic lesion possibly greater than 24 hours in duration).
24. Persistent hypertension with systolic BP greater than 185 mmHg or diastolic BP greater than 110 mmHg (mean of 3 consecutive arm cuff readings over 20-30 minutes), not controlled by antihypertensive therapy or requiring nitroprusside for control.
25. Anticipated need for major surgery within 72 hours after start of study drugs, e.g., carotid endarterectomy, hip fracture repair.
26. Any intracranial surgery, serious head trauma (any head injury that required hospitalization), within the past 3 months.
27. Stroke within the past 3 months.
28. History of ICH at any time in the past.
29. Major trauma at the time of stroke, e.g., hip fracture.
30. Blood glucose greater than 200 mg/dl.
31. Presence or history of intracranial neoplasm (except small meningiomas) or arteriovenous malformation.
32. Intracranial aneurysm, unless surgically treated greater than 3 months.
33. Major hemorrhage in past 21 days.
34. Major surgery, serious trauma, lumbar puncture, arterial puncture at a non-compressible site, or biopsy of a parenchymal organ in last 14 days.
35. Presumed or documented history of vasculitis.
36. Known systemic bleeding disorder, e.g., von Willebrand's disease, hemophilia, others.

Number of Criteria: 36

NCT03600714.inclusion:

INCLUSION CRITERIA:
1. Age 18 years or above, male or female.
2. Presence of anti-HDV in serum.
3. Presence of quantifiable HDV RNA in serum at three time pre-treatment points with a mean HDV RNA level >2 log10 above the lower limit of quantification (LLOQ) of the HDV RNA assay.
4. Demonstration of chronicity as evidenced by the presence of HDV RNA in serum for >/= 6 months, or presence of Anti-HDV antibody >/= 6months.

EXCLUSION CRITERIA:
1. Decompensated liver disease, defined by bilirubin >4mg/dL, albumin <3.0 gm/dL, prothrombin time >2 sec prolonged, or history of bleeding esophageal varices, ascites or hepatic encephalopathy. 
2. Pregnancy, active breast-feeding, or inability to practice adequate contraception, in women of childbearing potential or in partners of such women.
3. Significant systemic or major illnesses other than liver disease, including, but not limited to, congestive heart failure, renal failure (eGFR <50 ml/min), organ transplantation, serious psychiatric disease or depression, or active coronary artery disease.
4. Systemic immunosuppressive therapy within the previous 2 months before enrollment.
5. Evidence of another form of liver disease in addition to viral hepatitis.
6. Active substance abuse, such as alcohol, inhaled or injection drugs within the previous year.
7. Evidence of hepatocellular carcinoma.
8. Evidence of concurrent hepatitis C infection with positive serum hepatitis C virus (HCV) RNA.
9. Any experimental therapy or pegylated interferon therapy within 6 months prior to enrollment.
10. Active, serious autoimmune disease that might be exacerbated by therapy with lambda interferon.
11. Diagnosis of malignancy in the five years prior to the enrollment with exception granted to superficial dermatologic malignancies.
12. Evidence of HIV co-infection.
13. Concurrent usage of statins.
14. Concurrent usage of moderate and strong CYTOCHROME P-450 CYP3A (CYP3A) inhibitors and inducers.
15. Concurrent usage of certain drugs due to possible effect of ritonavir.
16. Clinically significant baseline EKG abnormalities.
17. Uncontrolled elevated triglycerides (>500 mg/dL).
18. History of pancreatitis from causes other than gallstone pancreatitis.
19. Inability to understand or sign informed consent.
20. Any other condition, which in the opinion of the investigators would impede the patient's participation or compliance in the study.
